Nkosinathi Ndlovu’s family is in shock after finding that her body has been lying in a government mortuary since December. The 22-year-old from Buyisonto, outside Thulamahashe in Mpumalanga, had been missing since 22 December. A relative, Prudence Ndlovu, told Daily Sun:“Early this month we saw a post by cops about a woman found dead and we arranged to see the body, only to find it was her. We hope cops arrest her killers.” Police spokesman Captain Sfiso Nyakane said a murder case is being investigated. Anyone with information is urged to contact Mhala cops on 013 773 0331 or Sergeant Daniel Khosa on 066 375 0458.